{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \"stats.json|dynamic-access|coverage|results.json|metrics|test_generation_failed|human intervention|manual|generated test|version-agnostic|exact library version|hardcode|hardcoded\" . || true'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \"stats.json|dynamic-access|coverage|results.json|metrics|test_generation_failed|human intervention|manual|generated test|version-agnostic|exact library version|hardcode|hardcoded\" . || true'","aggregated_output":"./COVERAGE.md:3:![Coverage over time](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/stats/coverage/latest/metrics-over-time.svg)\n./skills/README.md:22:It covers new-library metadata PRs, including titles like `[GenAI] Add support for com.fasterxml:classmate:1.5.1 using gpt-5.4`, and encodes the review rules already used in this repository: reject scaffold-only tests, keep test packages separate from library packages so tests do not bypass visibility boundaries, and question metadata coverage claims that are not supported by the diff.\n./skills/README.md:27:It covers compile-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the compile fix, preserve meaningful tests, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:32:It covers native-image runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: verify the native path is fixed rather than skipped, keep metadata and test changes scoped, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:60:in [Manual Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/dynamic-features/Reflection/#manual-configuration)\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:65:* Make sure that you are using [Conditional Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/metadata/#specifying-reflection-metadata-in-json)\n./docs/CI.md:24:  - Triggers: manual (workflow_dispatch) and PRs that touch [ci.json](../ci.json).\n./docs/CI.md:42:  - Triggers: scheduled run and manual ([`workflow_dispatch`](../.github/workflows/verify-new-library-version-compatibility.yml)).\n./docs/CI.md:49:- [.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml](../.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml): scheduled/manual workflow that generates repository coverage badges and the coverage dashboard from exploded stats files under [stats/](../stats/) and repository [metadata/**/index.json](../metadata/), then force-pushes the published artifacts to the `stats/coverage` branch. The published branch only keeps `latest/badges.json`, `latest/metrics-over-time.svg`, and `history/history.json`.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:29:To run the same coverage with future defaults enabled:\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:145:Generate coverage for the library under test exercised by our tests. Report contains coverage that focus exclusively on the provided library JARs, excluding unrelated external dependencies.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:166:- `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json`\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:179:- `validateLibraryStats`: validates mirrored committed stats files, schema compliance, and normalized sorting without recomputing metrics.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:279:- Generate dynamic access coverage report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:280:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\n./README.md:3:[![Libraries supported](https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=libraries%20supported&query=%24.badges.librariesSupported&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat-square&color=0A7EC2)](COVERAGE.md)\n./README.md:4:[![Tested library versions](https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=tested%20library%20versions&query=%24.badges.testedLibraryVersions&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat-square&color=BF8700)](COVERAGE.md)\n./README.md:5:[![Dynamic access coverage](https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=dynamic%20access%20coverage&query=%24.badges.dynamicAccessCoverage&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat-square&color=1F9D55)](COVERAGE.md)\n./README.md:6:[![Tested lines of code](https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=tested%20lines%20of%20code&query=%24.badges.testedLinesOfCode&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat-square&color=C2410C)](COVERAGE.md)\n./README.md:8:This repository provides [reachability metadata](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/metadata/) that lets Java libraries and frameworks work out of the box with [GraalVM Native Image](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/). \n./README.md:10:To get out-of-the-box support, use the [GraalVM Gradle Plugin](https://graalvm.github.io/native-build-tools/latest/gradle-plugin.html) or the [GraalVM Maven Plugin](https://graalvm.github.io/native-build-tools/latest/maven-plugin.html); they automatically use the [reachability metadata](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/metadata/) from this repository.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:19:- Do not accept tests that disable themselves under native image. If the added library behavior is guarded by checks such as `assumeFalse(\"runtime\".equals(System.getProperty(\"org.graalvm.nativeimage.imagecode\")))`, `if (!\"runtime\".equals(System.getProperty(\"org.graalvm.nativeimage.imagecode\")))`, or a similar native-only skip, then the PR does not provide native runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:20:- Do not accept tests that reference the exact library version in test code or assertions unless the version check is itself the behavior under test. One test should remain valid across multiple supported library versions.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:21:- Treat dynamic-access coverage counts as incomplete evidence. They can miss metadata required through downstream libraries, so do not reject a PR only because the exploded stats files under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` report `0/0` dynamic-access calls while the PR adds metadata.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:36:     - `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<new-version>/stats.json`\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject tests that hardcode the exact library version in strings, assertions, or expected output unless the test is explicitly validating version-dependent behavior.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:53:   - Do not use the exploded stats files under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` alone to argue that the submitted metadata is unnecessary.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:55:5. Compare the PR claims, test, and reported coverage as one unit.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:56:   - If the PR claims specific coverage numbers that do not line up with the diff, ask for investigation.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:57:   - If the PR reports zero dynamic-access calls and `reachability-metadata.json` is `{}`, that is acceptable as long as the test is library-specific and the scope is otherwise correct.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:69:  - The test logic is version-agnostic and can cover multiple supported versions of the same library.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:77:  - Test code hardcodes the target library version without a clear need.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:79:  - Claimed coverage is not credible from the diff.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:86:- For missing native runtime coverage: say that the added tests disable themselves under native image, so the library behavior never runs there and the PR does not provide native-image coverage.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:87:- For version-pinned tests: say that tests should not reference the exact library version because the same test should support multiple library versions.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:89:- For metadata/coverage mismatch: ask for investigation only when the PR makes concrete coverage claims that are not supported by the diff. Do not argue from metadata contents alone.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:35:     - `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/stats.json`\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:38:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `build.gradle`, `gradle.properties`, `settings.gradle`, and `user-code-filter.json` as normal when they live under the target version's test directory.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:50:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:51:   - Compare `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<old-metadata-version>/stats.json` and `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<new-metadata-version>/stats.json` when stats files are present in the PR or available on the branch.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:52:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:54:   - If metadata fixes make the native run pass but the dynamic-access ratio drops, ask for restored coverage first. Passing native execution is not enough by itself.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:55:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:61:   - Do not require an exact match. Small differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:62:   - Treat a large drop as blocking or at least requiring explanation when the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:77:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:83:- The fix makes native execution pass by skipping the failing native path, disabling assertions, or removing coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:93:- The API or native runtime change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:100:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:102:- For native skips: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair test sources or test dependencies after an existing library is bumped and the new version no longer compiles with the old test code. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to preserve working coverage across the version update rather than prove a brand-new metadata contribution from scratch.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept changes that remove meaningful test coverage just to make `javac` pass.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:35:     - `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<new-version>/stats.json`\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:39:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `build.gradle`, `gradle.properties`, `settings.gradle`, and `user-code-filter.json` as normal when they live under the target version's test directory.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:41:   - Reject or request changes if the PR removes tests, disables test classes, or drops assertions without replacing equivalent coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:49:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:50:   - Compare `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<old-metadata-version>/stats.json` and `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<new-metadata-version>/stats.json` when stats files are present in the PR or available on the branch.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:51:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:52:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:53:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - Do not require an exact match. Small differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - Treat a large drop as blocking or at least requiring explanation when the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:65:   - Prefer seeing the full target `test` lane green because a compile fix can still reduce runtime or native coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:75:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:82:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:91:- The API change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:98:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:100:- For deleted coverage: say that the PR fixes compilation by removing coverage and should instead adapt the test to the new API.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:16:- Close stale PRs with merge conflicts instead of repairing them manually if a newer bulk-update PR will supersede them.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:69:- `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` must point to the exact library version in the changed entry.\n./stats/org.reactivestreams/reactive-streams/1.0.3/stats.json:6:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/org.mariadb.jdbc/mariadb-java-client/3.0.6/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.473684,\n./stats/org.mariadb.jdbc/mariadb-java-client/3.0.6/stats.json:12:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.5,\n./stats/org.mariadb.jdbc/mariadb-java-client/3.0.6/stats.json:17:      \"coverageRatio\" : 0.47619,\n./stats/org.thymeleaf.extras/thymeleaf-extras-springsecurity6/3.1.0.RELEASE/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.5,\n./stats/org.thymeleaf.extras/thymeleaf-extras-springsecurity6/3.1.0.RELEASE/stats.json:12:      \"coverageRatio\" : 0.5,\n./stats/org.antlr/antlr4-runtime/4.10/stats.json:6:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/javax.interceptor/javax.interceptor-api/1.2/stats.json:6:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/org.mariadb.jdbc/mariadb-java-client/3.5.2/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.482759,\n./stats/org.mariadb.jdbc/mariadb-java-client/3.5.2/stats.json:12:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.333333,\n./stats/org.mariadb.jdbc/mariadb-java-client/3.5.2/stats.json:17:      \"coverageRatio\" : 0.46875,\n./stats/software.amazon.awssdk/s3/2.25.3/stats.json:6:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/org.example/library/0.0.1/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.5,\n./stats/org.example/library/0.0.1/stats.json:12:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.5,\n./stats/org.example/library/0.0.1/stats.json:17:      \"coverageRatio\" : 0.5,\n./stats/com.sun.istac